@dummdidumm Hello, Simon. I'm not sure why it happens exactly, my guess is because of `svelte-intl-precompile` together with SSR redirect to locale route. 

So basically `<svelte:head>` gets duplicated in such configuration as in the repo.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33694447/199935593-da3c514f-39c3-43cf-8fb6-476eee7954d4.png)

The problem is the HTML minifier in the `handle` hook which also removes comments. It seems that Svelte uses a header start/end comment to check its integrity. If that comment is removed, the hydration algorithm thinks that header is gone and appends it, duplicating the content.

The quick fix is to set the `removeComments` option to `false`.

@benmccann @tanhauhau I believe you were involved in some of the meta/header fixes, is there anything we can here other than telling people to not remove these comments?
